FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - IRAN
*********************************
A ProMED post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Foot & mouth disease - Iraq 990202174036
Foot & mouth disease - Iraq (06) 990504234427
Date: Fri, 01 Oct 1999 15:11:41 -0500
From: "Tam Garland" <TGARLAND@cvm.tamu.edu>
Source: OIE Reporting (24 Sept, 1999)

*****Virus type Asia 1 (additional information)*****
See also: 10 September 1999
Text of a fax received on 22 September 1999 from Dr Abbas Ali Motallebi,
Director of the Veterinary Organization of Iran, Tehran:
Report date: 8 September 1999.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 2 September 1999.
Estimated date of first infection: 30 August 1999.
Diagnosis: provisional laboratory diagnosis was made at the Central
Veterinary Laboratory of the Veterinary Organization of Iran and the Razi
Research Institute.
Virus type Asia 1 was confirmed by the OIE World Reference Laboratory for
foot and mouth disease (see Disease Information, 12 [35, 129, dated 10
September 1999).
Epidemiology: investigations are under way, in particular as to the origin
of the disease.
Control measures during reporting period:
- All infected cattle were destroyed.
- Vaccination with a monovalent FMD vaccine of Asia 1 serotype within an
appropriate radius has been implemented.
- The area has been placed under strict quarantine regulations.
- The surveillance system has been strengthened in the affected area and the
neighbouring regions.
--
ProMED
<promed@usa.healthnet.org>
